                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-07-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 14, 1904</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. White states that the British foreign office desires to know what measures,
                    if any, the United States Government proposes to take to protect seals in
                    Russian waters against American raiders as provided for in the act of Congress
                    of 1897, which prohibits American citizens and persons belonging to American
                    vessels from killing or capturing seals in the North Pacific Ocean, including
                    Bering Sea and the Sea of Okhotsk.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
